## Requirements

```
ultralytics
opencv-python
numpy
pyserial
```

```bash
pip install ultralytics opencv-python numpy pyserial
```

A trained YOLOv8 weights file named **`best.pt`** must be placed in the working directory.

---

## Usage

```bash
python pot_detection_theta.py
```

- Reads from a live camera (`CAMERA_INDEX`) or a video file (`VIDEO_PATH`).
- Displays a live annotated window (detected pots, fitted lane center, current θ).
- Logs per-frame results to `theta_real_dist_log.csv`:

| frame | theta_deg | dx_meters | status |
|---|---|---|---|
| frame index | smoothed, clamped steering angle | lateral offset in meters | `NORMAL` / `EMERGENCY_TURN` |

---

## Notes

- Accurate real-world θ depends on correct camera calibration (`CAMERA_HEIGHT_M`, `TARGET_DIST_M`, `PXM_RATIO_AT_TARGET`) for the specific camera mounting height and angle.
- The script also includes a front-point collision check and emergency-turn override, and streams the resulting θ to an Arduino over serial for closed-loop steering control — these run alongside the detection/theta pipeline described above.

